  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Polyaenus, 2, Rhetor, c. 60 B.C.,Sophist, active c. 60 BC, author 
    of a lost Θρίαμβος Παρθικός (Thríambos Parthikós), in 3 books, probably on the victory over the Parthians in 38 BC. 
    He is generally identified with the author (cf. Suda s. v. Πολύαινος Σαρδιανός) to whom a sophisticated epigram in the
    style of Leonidas of Tarentum (Anth. Pal. 9,1) is attributed." Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna"Polyaenus." Brill's New Pauly. 
    Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2010. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 28 October 2010</mads:note>  
